# Product UX

## Visual tone

- Background: warm parchment, not flat Material gray/purple
- Characters on thin tiles (mahjong-inspired but flatter/thinner)
- Avoid gamified chrome; light progress stats are OK

## Study / reading tiles

- Word groups visual; user merge/split remembered
- Pinyin on study tiles: settings toggle; when on, small pinyin under the character
- Multi-sense glosses; never collapse to one “best” English

## Memorize

- Configurable hints; exhausting hints → clear/reset that attempt
- Hint styles: narrow choice pool and/or flash up to 3 candidates (one correct)
- Stats: current and best chars filled for current paragraph/sentence lifetime only

## Stroke practice

- Large canvas; pinyin always at bottom of canvas
- Small icons for translation and scholar deep-dive (radicals, senses, related forms)
- Hint flashes next stroke; exhausting hints → fail that attempt
- Per-character stroke stats stored indefinitely
